                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_balc" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>balc</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>balci</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отлучка из дому</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>absence from home</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>поездка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>trip</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>путешествие</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>journey</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>balcy cæwyn</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>отправляться в поездку</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>start on one's journey</q></tr></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>bælccon</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>путник</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>traveller</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>balcy zaræg</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">походная песня</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">camp song</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Wyryzmæǵy fæstag balc</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>последняя поездка Урузмага</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Wyryzmæg's last trip</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>jæ fæstag balcy, kæmdær, Qobany dær wyd Tægiatæm</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в последнюю поездку он, оказывается, побывал также в (ауле) Кобан у Тагаурцев</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>it turned out that during his last trip he also visited the Tægiatæ in the village Qoban</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>140</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>idard balci bakodtan oni fæwwinunmæ bælgæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мы совершили дальнюю поездку, стремясь увидеть их</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>we made a long journey craving for seeing them</q></tr></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Subalci randæj kʼwære balci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Субалци отправился в недельную поездку</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Subalci started on his week journey</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 76</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>næ bælccættæ ægas xæʒar yssarænt</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пусть наши путники благополучно вернутся домой!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>may our travellers come home safely!</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>balcy zaræg</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">походная песня</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q rendition="rend_singlequotes">camp song</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>34</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Wyryzmæǵy fæstag balc</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>последняя поездка Урузмага</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Wyryzmæg's last trip</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>jæ fæstag balcy, kæmdær, Qobany dær wyd Tægiatæm</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>в последнюю поездку он, оказывается, побывал также в (ауле) Кобан у Тагаурцев</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>it turned out that during his last trip he also visited the Tægiatæ in the village Qoban</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>140</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>idard balci bakodtan oni fæwwinunmæ bælgæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>мы совершили дальнюю поездку, стремясь увидеть их</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>we made a long journey craving for seeing them</q></tr></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>Subalci randæj kʼwære balci</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Субалци отправился в недельную поездку</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Subalci started on his week journey</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 76</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>næ bælccættæ ægas xæʒar yssarænt</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пусть наши путники благополучно вернутся домой!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>may our travellers come home safely!</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Возводится к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*bārti-</w> <gloss><q>поездка верхом</q></gloss></mentioned> (от %ibār%i- [см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8bar"/>] ‘ездить верхом’, см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bajrag"/>). По образованию ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xælc"/> из *%ixvarti%i-. В дигорском ожидали бы %ibalcæ%i. В ближайшей связи c %ibalc%i находятся слова <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bal"/> ‘(военная) партия’, ‘отряд’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_balxon"/> ‘вожак военной партии’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmbal"/> ‘товарищ’. Все они восходят к эпохе военной демократии.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>5</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>573</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The word traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*bārti-</w> <gloss><q>riding</q></gloss></mentioned> (from %ibār%i- [see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_8bar"/>] ‘ride’, see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bajrag"/>). Cf. by formation <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xælc"/> from *%ixvarti%i-. In Digor the word should look like %ibalcæ%i. The following words are in the closest relation with the word %ibalc%i: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bal"/> ‘(war) party’, ‘troop’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_balxon"/> ‘leader of a war party’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æmbal"/> ‘comrade’. All of these words are related to the times of military democracy. %n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"/><biblScope>5</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>573</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>